  97. ‌let add_used_primitive loc env path =
  98.   match path with
  99.     Some (Path.Pdot _ as path) ->
  100.       let path = Env.normalize_value_path (Some loc) env path in
  101.       let unit = Path.head path in
  102.       if Ident.global unit && not (Hashtbl.mem used_primitives path)
  103.       then Hashtbl.add used_primitives path loc
  104.   | _ -> ()

  369.     "%atomic_cas", Primitive (Patomic_cas, 3);

  379. let lookup_primitive loc p =

  381.   | prim -> prim
  382.   | exception Not_found ->

  384.         raise(Error(loc, Unknown_builtin_primitive p.prim_name));

  392. ‌let simplify_constant_constructor = function
  393.   | Equal -> true
  394.   | Not_equal -> true
  395.   | Less_equal -> false
  396.   | Less_than -> false
  397.   | Greater_equal -> false
  398.   | Greater_than -> false
  399.   | Compare -> false

  401. (* The following function computes the greatest lower bound in the
  402.    semilattice of array kinds:
  403.           gen
  404.          /   \
  405.       addr   float
  406.        |
  407.       int
  408.    Note that the GLB is not guaranteed to exist, in which case we return
  409.    our first argument instead of raising a fatal error because, although
  410.    it cannot happen in a well-typed program, (ab)use of Obj.magic can
  411.    probably trigger it.
  412. *)
  413. ‌let glb_array_type t1 t2 =
  414.   match t1, t2 with
  415.   | Pfloatarray, (Paddrarray | Pintarray)
  416.   | (Paddrarray | Pintarray), Pfloatarray -> t1

  418.   | Pgenarray, x | x, Pgenarray -> x
  419.   | Paddrarray, x | x, Paddrarray -> x
  420.   | Pintarray, Pintarray -> Pintarray
  421.   | Pfloatarray, Pfloatarray -> Pfloatarray

  423. (* Specialize a primitive from available type information. *)

  425. ‌let specialize_primitive env ty ~has_constant_constructor prim =
  426.   let param_tys =
  427.     match is_function_type env ty with
  428.     | None -> []
  429.     | Some (p1, rhs) ->
  430.       match is_function_type env rhs with
  431.       | None -> [p1]
  432.       | Some (p2, _) -> [p1;p2]
  433.   in
  434.   match prim, param_tys with
  435.   | Primitive (Psetfield(n, Pointer, init), arity), [_; p2] -> begin
  436.       match maybe_pointer_type env p2 with
  437.       | Pointer -> None
  438.       | Immediate -> Some (Primitive (Psetfield(n, Immediate, init), arity))
  439.     end
  440.   | Primitive (Pfield (n, Pointer, mut), arity), _ ->
  441.       (* try strength reduction based on the *result type* *)
  442.       let is_int = match is_function_type env ty with
  443.         | None -> Pointer
  444.         | Some (_p1, rhs) -> maybe_pointer_type env rhs in
  445.       Some (Primitive (Pfield (n, is_int, mut), arity))
  446.   | Primitive (Parraylength t, arity), [p] -> begin
  447.       let array_type = glb_array_type t (array_type_kind env p) in
  448.       if t = array_type then None
  449.       else Some (Primitive (Parraylength array_type, arity))
  450.     end
  451.   | Primitive (Parrayrefu t, arity), p1 :: _ -> begin
  452.       let array_type = glb_array_type t (array_type_kind env p1) in
  453.       if t = array_type then None
  454.       else Some (Primitive (Parrayrefu array_type, arity))
  455.     end
  456.   | Primitive (Parraysetu t, arity), p1 :: _ -> begin
  457. ‌      let array_type = glb_array_type t (array_type_kind env p1) in
  458.       if t = array_type then None
  459.       else Some (Primitive (Parraysetu array_type, arity))
  460.     end
  461.   | Primitive (Parrayrefs t, arity), p1 :: _ -> begin
  462. ‌      let array_type = glb_array_type t (array_type_kind env p1) in
  463.       if t = array_type then None
  464.       else Some (Primitive (Parrayrefs array_type, arity))
  465.     end
  466.   | Primitive (Parraysets t, arity), p1 :: _ -> begin
  467. ‌      let array_type = glb_array_type t (array_type_kind env p1) in
  468.       if t = array_type then None
  469.       else Some (Primitive (Parraysets array_type, arity))
  470.     end
  471.   | Primitive (Pbigarrayref(unsafe, n, Pbigarray_unknown,
  472.                             Pbigarray_unknown_layout), arity), p1 :: _ -> begin
  473. ‌      let (k, l) = bigarray_type_kind_and_layout env p1 in
  474.       match k, l with
  475.       | Pbigarray_unknown, Pbigarray_unknown_layout -> None
  476.       | _, _ -> Some (Primitive (Pbigarrayref(unsafe, n, k, l), arity))
  477.     end
  478.   | Primitive (Pbigarrayset(unsafe, n, Pbigarray_unknown,
  479.                             Pbigarray_unknown_layout), arity), p1 :: _ -> begin
  480. ‌      let (k, l) = bigarray_type_kind_and_layout env p1 in
  481.       match k, l with
  482.       | Pbigarray_unknown, Pbigarray_unknown_layout -> None
  483.       | _, _ -> Some (Primitive (Pbigarrayset(unsafe, n, k, l), arity))
  484.     end
  485.   | Primitive (Pmakeblock(tag, mut, None), arity), fields -> begin
  486. ‌      let shape = List.map (Typeopt.value_kind env) fields in
  487. ‌      let useful = List.exists (fun knd -> knd <> Pgenval) shape in
  488.       if useful then Some (Primitive (Pmakeblock(tag, mut, Some shape), arity))
  489.       else None
  490.     end
  491.   | Primitive (Patomic_load { immediate_or_pointer = Pointer },
  492.                arity), _ ->begin
  493. ‌      let is_int = match is_function_type env ty with
  494.         | None -> Pointer
  495.         | Some (_p1, rhs) -> maybe_pointer_type env rhs in
  496.       Some (Primitive (Patomic_load {immediate_or_pointer = is_int}, arity))
  497.     end
  498.   | Comparison(comp, Compare_generic), p1 :: _ ->
  499.     if (has_constant_constructor
  500.         && simplify_constant_constructor comp) then begin
  501.       Some (Comparison(comp, Compare_ints))
  502.     end else if (is_base_type env p1 Predef.path_int
  503.         || is_base_type env p1 Predef.path_char
  504.         || (maybe_pointer_type env p1 = Immediate)) then begin
  505.       Some (Comparison(comp, Compare_ints))
  506.     end else if is_base_type env p1 Predef.path_float then begin
  507.       Some (Comparison(comp, Compare_floats))
  508.     end else if is_base_type env p1 Predef.path_string then begin
  509.       Some (Comparison(comp, Compare_strings))
  510.     end else if is_base_type env p1 Predef.path_bytes then begin
  511.       Some (Comparison(comp, Compare_bytes))
  512.     end else if is_base_type env p1 Predef.path_nativeint then begin
  513.       Some (Comparison(comp, Compare_nativeints))
  514.     end else if is_base_type env p1 Predef.path_int32 then begin
  515.       Some (Comparison(comp, Compare_int32s))
  516.     end else if is_base_type env p1 Predef.path_int64 then begin
  517.       Some (Comparison(comp, Compare_int64s))
  518.     end else begin
  519.       None
  520.     end
  521.   | _ -> None

  566. ‌let comparison_primitive comparison comparison_kind =
  567.   match comparison, comparison_kind with
  568.   | Equal, Compare_generic -> Pccall caml_equal
  569.   | Equal, Compare_ints -> Pintcomp Ceq
  570.   | Equal, Compare_floats -> Pfloatcomp CFeq
  571.   | Equal, Compare_strings -> Pccall caml_string_equal
  572.   | Equal, Compare_bytes -> Pccall caml_bytes_equal
  573.   | Equal, Compare_nativeints -> Pbintcomp(Pnativeint, Ceq)
  574.   | Equal, Compare_int32s -> Pbintcomp(Pint32, Ceq)
  575.   | Equal, Compare_int64s -> Pbintcomp(Pint64, Ceq)
  576.   | Not_equal, Compare_generic -> Pccall caml_notequal
  577.   | Not_equal, Compare_ints -> Pintcomp Cne
  578.   | Not_equal, Compare_floats -> Pfloatcomp CFneq
  579.   | Not_equal, Compare_strings -> Pccall caml_string_notequal
  580.   | Not_equal, Compare_bytes -> Pccall caml_bytes_notequal
  581.   | Not_equal, Compare_nativeints -> Pbintcomp(Pnativeint, Cne)
  582.   | Not_equal, Compare_int32s -> Pbintcomp(Pint32, Cne)
  583.   | Not_equal, Compare_int64s -> Pbintcomp(Pint64, Cne)
  584.   | Less_equal, Compare_generic -> Pccall caml_lessequal
  585.   | Less_equal, Compare_ints -> Pintcomp Cle
  586.   | Less_equal, Compare_floats -> Pfloatcomp CFle
  587.   | Less_equal, Compare_strings -> Pccall caml_string_lessequal
  588.   | Less_equal, Compare_bytes -> Pccall caml_bytes_lessequal
  589.   | Less_equal, Compare_nativeints -> Pbintcomp(Pnativeint, Cle)
  590.   | Less_equal, Compare_int32s -> Pbintcomp(Pint32, Cle)
  591.   | Less_equal, Compare_int64s -> Pbintcomp(Pint64, Cle)
  592.   | Less_than, Compare_generic -> Pccall caml_lessthan
  593.   | Less_than, Compare_ints -> Pintcomp Clt
  594.   | Less_than, Compare_floats -> Pfloatcomp CFlt
  595.   | Less_than, Compare_strings -> Pccall caml_string_lessthan
  596.   | Less_than, Compare_bytes -> Pccall caml_bytes_lessthan
  597.   | Less_than, Compare_nativeints -> Pbintcomp(Pnativeint, Clt)
  598.   | Less_than, Compare_int32s -> Pbintcomp(Pint32, Clt)
  599.   | Less_than, Compare_int64s -> Pbintcomp(Pint64, Clt)
  600.   | Greater_equal, Compare_generic -> Pccall caml_greaterequal
  601.   | Greater_equal, Compare_ints -> Pintcomp Cge
  602.   | Greater_equal, Compare_floats -> Pfloatcomp CFge
  603.   | Greater_equal, Compare_strings -> Pccall caml_string_greaterequal
  604.   | Greater_equal, Compare_bytes -> Pccall caml_bytes_greaterequal
  605.   | Greater_equal, Compare_nativeints -> Pbintcomp(Pnativeint, Cge)
  606.   | Greater_equal, Compare_int32s -> Pbintcomp(Pint32, Cge)
  607.   | Greater_equal, Compare_int64s -> Pbintcomp(Pint64, Cge)
  608.   | Greater_than, Compare_generic -> Pccall caml_greaterthan
  609.   | Greater_than, Compare_ints -> Pintcomp Cgt
  610.   | Greater_than, Compare_floats -> Pfloatcomp CFgt
  611.   | Greater_than, Compare_strings -> Pccall caml_string_greaterthan
  612.   | Greater_than, Compare_bytes -> Pccall caml_bytes_greaterthan
  613.   | Greater_than, Compare_nativeints -> Pbintcomp(Pnativeint, Cgt)
  614.   | Greater_than, Compare_int32s -> Pbintcomp(Pint32, Cgt)
  615.   | Greater_than, Compare_int64s -> Pbintcomp(Pint64, Cgt)
  616.   | Compare, Compare_generic -> Pccall caml_compare
  617.   | Compare, Compare_ints -> Pcompare_ints
  618.   | Compare, Compare_floats -> Pcompare_floats
  619.   | Compare, Compare_strings -> Pccall caml_string_compare
  620.   | Compare, Compare_bytes -> Pccall caml_bytes_compare
  621.   | Compare, Compare_nativeints -> Pcompare_bints Pnativeint
  622.   | Compare, Compare_int32s -> Pcompare_bints Pint32
  623.   | Compare, Compare_int64s -> Pcompare_bints Pint64

  625. ‌let lambda_of_loc kind sloc =

  628.   let (file, lnum, cnum) = Location.get_pos_info loc_start in

  630.     if Filename.is_relative file then
  631.       file
  632.     else
  633.       Location.rewrite_absolute_path file in
  634. ‌  let enum = loc.Location.loc_end.Lexing.pos_cnum -
  635.       loc_start.Lexing.pos_cnum + cnum in
  636.   match kind with
  637.   | Loc_POS ->

  639.           Const_immstring file;
  640.           Const_base (Const_int lnum);
  641.           Const_base (Const_int cnum);
  642.           Const_base (Const_int enum);
  643.         ]))
  644.   | Loc_FILE -> Lconst (Const_immstring file)
  645.   | Loc_MODULE ->

  652.         file lnum cnum enum in

  654.   | Loc_LINE -> Lconst (Const_base (Const_int lnum))
  655.   | Loc_FUNCTION ->

  659. ‌let caml_restore_raw_backtrace =
  660.   Primitive.simple ~name:"caml_restore_raw_backtrace" ~arity:2 ~alloc:false

  662. ‌let try_ids = Hashtbl.create 8

  664. ‌let add_exception_ident id =
  665.   Hashtbl.replace try_ids id ()

  667. ‌let remove_exception_ident id =
  668.   Hashtbl.remove try_ids id

  670. ‌let lambda_of_prim prim_name prim loc args arg_exps =
  671.   match prim, args with
  672.   | Primitive (prim, arity), args when arity = List.length args ->
  673.       Lprim(prim, args, loc)
  674.   | External prim, args when prim = prim_sys_argv ->
  675.       Lprim(Pccall prim, Lconst (const_int 0) :: args, loc)
  676.   | External prim, args ->
  677.       Lprim(Pccall prim, args, loc)
  678.   | Comparison(comp, knd), ([_;_] as args) ->
  679.       let prim = comparison_primitive comp knd in
  680.       Lprim(prim, args, loc)
  681.   | Raise kind, [arg] ->
  682.       let kind =
  683.         match kind, arg with
  684.         | Raise_regular, Lvar argv when Hashtbl.mem try_ids argv ->
  685.             Raise_reraise
  686.         | _, _ ->
  687.             kind
  688.       in
  689.       let arg =
  690.         match arg_exps with
  691.         | None -> arg
  692.         | Some [arg_exp] -> event_after loc arg_exp arg
  693.         | Some _ -> assert false
  694.       in
  695.       Lprim(Praise kind, [arg], loc)
  696.   | Raise_with_backtrace, [exn; bt] ->
  697.       let vexn = Ident.create_local "exn" in
  698.       let raise_arg =
  699.         match arg_exps with
  700.         | None -> Lvar vexn
  701.         | Some [exn_exp; _] -> event_after loc exn_exp (Lvar vexn)
  702.         | Some _ -> assert false
  703.       in
  704.       Llet(Strict, Pgenval, vexn, exn,
  705.            Lsequence(Lprim(Pccall caml_restore_raw_backtrace,
  706.                            [Lvar vexn; bt],
  707.                            loc),
  708.                      Lprim(Praise Raise_reraise, [raise_arg], loc)))
  709.   | Lazy_force, [arg] ->
  710.       Matching.inline_lazy_force arg loc
  711.   | Loc kind, [] ->
  712.       lambda_of_loc kind loc
  713.   | Loc kind, [arg] ->
  714.       let lam = lambda_of_loc kind loc in
  715.       Lprim(Pmakeblock(0, Immutable, None), [lam; arg], loc)
  716.   | Send, [obj; meth] ->
  717.       Lsend(Public, meth, obj, [], loc)
  718.   | Send_self, [obj; meth] ->
  719.       Lsend(Self, meth, obj, [], loc)
  720.   | Send_cache, [obj; meth; cache; pos] ->
  721.       (* Cached mode only works in the native backend *)
  722.       if !Clflags.native_code then
  723.         Lsend(Cached, meth, obj, [cache; pos], loc)
  724.       else
  725.         Lsend(Public, meth, obj, [], loc)
  726.   | Frame_pointers, [] ->
  727. ‌      let frame_pointers =
  728.         if !Clflags.native_code && Config.with_frame_pointers then 1 else 0
  729.       in
  730.       Lconst (const_int frame_pointers)
  731.   | Identity, [arg] -> arg
  732.   | Apply, [func; arg]
  733.   | Revapply, [arg; func] ->
  734.       Lapply {
  735.         ap_func = func;
  736.         ap_args = [arg];
  737.         ap_loc = loc;
  738.         (* CR-someday lwhite: it would be nice to be able to give
  739.            application attributes to functions applied with the application
  740.            operators. *)
  741.         ap_tailcall = Default_tailcall;
  742.         ap_inlined = Default_inline;
  743.         ap_specialised = Default_specialise;
  744.       }
  745.   | (Raise _ | Raise_with_backtrace
  746.     | Lazy_force | Loc _ | Primitive _ | Comparison _
  747.     | Send | Send_self | Send_cache | Frame_pointers | Identity
  748.     | Apply | Revapply), _ ->
  749.       raise(Error(to_location loc, Wrong_arity_builtin_primitive prim_name))

  751. ‌let check_primitive_arity loc p =
  752.   let prim = lookup_primitive loc p in
  753.   let ok =
  754.     match prim with
  755.     | Primitive (_,arity) -> arity = p.prim_arity
  756.     | External _ -> true
  757.     | Comparison _ -> p.prim_arity = 2
  758.     | Raise _ -> p.prim_arity = 1
  759.     | Raise_with_backtrace -> p.prim_arity = 2
  760.     | Lazy_force -> p.prim_arity = 1
  761.     | Loc _ -> p.prim_arity = 1 || p.prim_arity = 0
  762.     | Send | Send_self -> p.prim_arity = 2
  763.     | Send_cache -> p.prim_arity = 4
  764.     | Frame_pointers -> p.prim_arity = 0
  765.     | Identity -> p.prim_arity = 1
  766.     | Apply | Revapply -> p.prim_arity = 2
  767.   in
  768.   if not ok then raise(Error(loc, Wrong_arity_builtin_primitive p.prim_name))

  770. (* Eta-expand a primitive *)

  772. ‌let transl_primitive loc p env ty path =
  773.   let prim = lookup_primitive_and_mark_used (to_location loc) p env path in
  774.   let has_constant_constructor = false in
  775.   let prim =
  776.     match specialize_primitive env ty ~has_constant_constructor prim with
  777.     | None -> prim
  778.     | Some prim -> prim
  779.   in
  780.   let rec make_params n =
  781.     if n <= 0 then []
  782.     else (Ident.create_local "prim", Pgenval) :: make_params (n-1)
  783.   in
  784. ‌  let params = make_params p.prim_arity in
  785. ‌  let args = List.map (fun (id, _) -> Lvar id) params in
  786. ‌  let body = lambda_of_prim p.prim_name prim loc args None in
  787.   match params with
  788.   | [] -> body
  789.   | _ ->
  790.       lfunction ~kind:Curried
  791.                 ~params
  792.                 ~return:Pgenval
  793.                 ~attr:default_stub_attribute
  794.                 ~loc
  795.                 ~body

  797. ‌let lambda_primitive_needs_event_after = function
  798.   (* We add an event after any primitive resulting in a C call that
  799.      may raise an exception or allocate. These are places where we may
  800.      collect the call stack. *)
  801.   | Pduprecord _ | Pccall _ | Pfloatofint | Pnegfloat | Pabsfloat

  829.       -> false

  831. (* Determine if a primitive should be surrounded by an "after" debug event *)
  832. ‌let primitive_needs_event_after = function
  833.   | Primitive (prim,_) -> lambda_primitive_needs_event_after prim
  834.   | External _ -> true
  835.   | Comparison(comp, knd) ->
  836.       lambda_primitive_needs_event_after (comparison_primitive comp knd)
  837.   | Lazy_force | Send | Send_self | Send_cache
  838.   | Apply | Revapply -> true
  839.   | Raise _ | Raise_with_backtrace | Loc _ | Frame_pointers | Identity -> false

  841. ‌let transl_primitive_application loc p env ty path exp args arg_exps =
  842.   let prim =
  843.     lookup_primitive_and_mark_used (to_location loc) p env (Some path) in
  844.   let has_constant_constructor =
  845.     match arg_exps with
  846.     | [_; {exp_desc = Texp_construct(_, {cstr_tag = Cstr_constant _}, _)}]
  847.     | [{exp_desc = Texp_construct(_, {cstr_tag = Cstr_constant _}, _)}; _]
  848.     | [_; {exp_desc = Texp_variant(_, None)}]
  849.     | [{exp_desc = Texp_variant(_, None)}; _] -> true
  850.     | _ -> false
  851.   in
  852.   let prim =
  853.     match specialize_primitive env ty ~has_constant_constructor prim with
  854.     | None -> prim
  855.     | Some prim -> prim
  856.   in
  857.   let lam = lambda_of_prim p.prim_name prim loc args (Some arg_exps) in
  858.   let lam =
  859.     if primitive_needs_event_after prim then begin
  860.       match exp with
  861.       | None -> lam
  862.       | Some exp -> event_after loc exp lam
  863.     end else begin
  864.       lam
  865.     end
  866.   in
  867.   lam

  869. (* Error report *)

  871. open Format

  873. ‌let report_error ppf = function
  874.   | Unknown_builtin_primitive prim_name ->
  875.       fprintf ppf "Unknown builtin primitive \"%s\"" prim_name
  876.   | Wrong_arity_builtin_primitive prim_name ->
  877.       fprintf ppf "Wrong arity for builtin primitive \"%s\"" prim_name

  879. let () =
  880.   Location.register_error_of_exn
  881.     (function
  882.       | Error (loc, err) ->
  883.           Some (Location.error_of_printer ~loc report_error err)
  884.       | _ ->
  885.         None
  886.     )
